==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embolus
<hw>Em"bo*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Emboli</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/ pointed so
as to be put or thrust in, fr. <?/ to throw, thrust, or put in. See
<er>Emblem</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Something inserted, as a wedge;
the piston or sucker of a pump or syringe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A plug of some substance lodged in
a blood vessel, being brought thither by the blood current. It consists
most frequently of a clot of fibrin, a detached shred of a morbid
growth, a globule of fat, or a microscopic organism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emboly</ent>⟦br⟧
